= RETINA Cell Counter =
<br>
RETINA Cell Counter is a customizable tool that processes digital images from retinal cryosections. It segments retinal outer nuclear (ONL) and inner nuclear layers (INL) and quantitates fluorescent-labelled cells in these layers. The validation process of the first version of this macro (TUNEL Cell Counter) can be found in our ''Investigative Ophthalmology & Visual Science (IOVS)'' paper. 
[[Image:RETINA Cell Counter Montage.png |thumb|center|1200px|'''RETINA Cell Counter''': Input a fluorescent-labeled retinal image for ONL & INL layer segmentation and cell quantitation.]]



== Setup ==
The following are required to execute this tool: 
#RETINA Cell Counter installed in Fiji (ImageJ).
#Digital Image in TIFF format.
#Microscope Spatial Scale (pixels/microns). 
#Minimum Cell Size & Maximum Cell Area (µm<sup>2</sup>): These should be determined upfront, according to your image dataset. This measurements can be performed in Fiji with the freehand selection tool, after setting the spatial scale factor.

